<section class="tw-section tw-mwhy" id="why">
  <div class="tw-container">
    <div class="tw-section-head-left">
      <div class="tw-eyebrow" style="color:var(--tw-sage)">Why owners choose Tidewater Maintenance</div>
      <h2 class="tw-section-title">A handyman fixes the leak. <em>We fix the leak, document the claim, and know your county&rsquo;s smoke-detector rule.</em></h2>
      <p class="tw-section-lede">Four things that separate Tidewater Property Maintenance from the average contractor pulled off a directory site.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="tw-mwhy-grid">
      <article class="tw-mwhy-card feat">
        <div class="tw-mwhy-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><path d="M12 2l8 4v6c0 5-3.5 9-8 10-4.5-1-8-5-8-10V6l8-4z"/><path d="M9 12l2 2 4-4"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="tw-mwhy-num">01 &middot; Cross-Portfolio Compliance</div>
        <h3 class="tw-mwhy-title">We don&rsquo;t just fix the smoke detector. <em>We know which one your county requires.</em></h3>
        <p class="tw-mwhy-copy">Our technicians work across Tidewater&rsquo;s full rental portfolio every day. They know <strong>Baltimore City&rsquo;s lead-paint registration</strong>, <strong>Montgomery County&rsquo;s rental license inspections</strong>, and the smoke-detector rule that just changed last legislative session. A contractor from a general directory can do the repair. We can do the repair <em>and</em> keep your property licensable.</p>
        <div class="tw-mwhy-foot">
          <strong>Where it shows up:</strong> when a tenant files a habitability complaint and your contractor&rsquo;s receipts don&rsquo;t match what your county actually requires.
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="tw-mwhy-card">
        <div class="tw-mwhy-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><path d="M19 16.9A5 5 0 0 0 18 7h-1.26a8 8 0 1 0-11.62 9"/><polyline points="13 11 9 17 15 17 11 23"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="tw-mwhy-num">02 &middot; Mitigation Capacity</div>
        <h3 class="tw-mwhy-title">When other mitigation companies are out, <em>we&rsquo;re still showing up.</em></h3>
        <p class="tw-mwhy-copy">During the last deep-freeze event we expanded our mitigation equipment to serve communities when outside companies were fully committed. <strong>Water damage, flood response, emergency repairs</strong> &mdash; our crews are equipped to mitigate, not just diagnose.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="tw-mwhy-card">
        <div class="tw-mwhy-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><path d="M12 3v18"/><path d="M8 9l-4 3 4 3"/><path d="M16 9l4 3-4 3"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="tw-mwhy-num">03 &middot; Not Mandatory. Just Vetted.</div>
        <h3 class="tw-mwhy-title">We bid <em>alongside</em> your other vendors, not against them.</h3>
        <p class="tw-mwhy-copy">Tidewater clients are never required to use Tidewater Maintenance. For larger projects we obtain competitive bids from outside vendors alongside ours &mdash; so boards see real options. <strong>Rental clients receive a discount off standard rates.</strong> A captive vendor wouldn&rsquo;t need to compete; we do.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="tw-mwhy-card">
        <div class="tw-mwhy-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><path d="M1 12s4-8 11-8 11 8 11 8-4 8-11 8-11-8-11-8z"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="tw-mwhy-num">04 &middot; Proactive Property Visits</div>
        <h3 class="tw-mwhy-title">Regular walks. <em>Not just reactive calls.</em></h3>
        <p class="tw-mwhy-copy">We inspect for quality and compliance on a scheduled cadence &mdash; the same proactive maintenance philosophy that runs through Tidewater&rsquo;s HOA and rental management. <strong>Small issues caught at walk #2</strong> stay off your repair invoice in month nine.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
